After {{ill|World War II|ja|第二次世界大戦|12=draft|12=draft}}, changes in labor laws such as the strengthening of the {{ill|Labour Standards Act|ja|労働基準法|12=draft|12=draft}} and the adoption of the {{ill|five-day workweek|ja|週休2日制|12=draft|12=draft}} led to the decline of Yabuiri. Instead, it was absorbed into the longer {{ill|New Year holidays|ja|正月休み|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Obon holidays|ja|盆休み|12=draft|12=draft}}, surviving mainly as the tradition of {{ill|returning home for the holidays|ja|帰省|12=draft|12=draft}}.

