On Yabuiri, the master of the household would give his servants gifts such as new {{ill|kimono|ja|着物|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|footwear|ja|履物|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, spending money, and souvenirs to take home<ref name="koubunkan" />. The servants would then return to their family homes to spend the day with their parents. For those who had traveled long distances for work or had reached adulthood and could not return home, the day was spent enjoying entertainment such as {{ill|kabuki|ja|芝居|qq=draft|qq=draft}} performances or shopping.

